"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-world-2024-0927-1472283-paris-olympics-eiffel-tower\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Workers in Paris have removed the Olympics logo from the Eiffel Tower, returning the beloved monument to its usual form - but perhaps only temporarily.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983829184, \"rank\": 1.6171344771300424e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Workers\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 7}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics logo\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 69}, {\"ngram\": \"the beloved monument\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 101}, {\"ngram\": \"its usual form\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo has promised to build new Olympic rings and return them to the landmark as a tribute to the hugely successful Olympic Games held over the summer.\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 165, \"end\": 177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"new Olympic rings\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 217}, {\"ngram\": \"the landmark\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 249}, {\"ngram\": \"a tribute\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"the hugely successful Olympic Games\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The proposition has been criticised by descendants of the tower's designer Gustave Eiffel, as well as conservation groups and many Parisians.\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustave Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The proposition\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"descendants\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"conservation groups\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"many Parisians\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After initially suggesting the rings should be permanent, Ms Hidalgo has proposed they remain on the city's best-known symbol until the next Olympics in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999951785917162, \"rank\": 4.510326605198688e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's best-known symbol\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"the next Olympics\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Workers using a crane removed the 30-tonne rings from between the first and second floors of the tower overnight, just under four months after they were put up on 7 June.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Workers\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"a crane\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"the 30-tonne rings\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 691}, {\"ngram\": \"the first and second floors\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"7 June\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new rings, which the International Olympic Committee is expected to pay for, would be lighter versions and less prominent, according to a deputy Paris mayor, Pierre Rabadan.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983829184, \"rank\": 1.6171344771300424e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre Rabadan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_Rabadan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new rings\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"lighter versions\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Culture Minister Rachida Dati, a longtime critic and opponent of Ms Hidalgo, has cast doubt over the idea, saying the Socialist city leader would need to respect procedures protecting historic buildings.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}, {\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a longtime critic\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"opponent\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"doubt\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1103}, {\"ngram\": \"the Socialist city leader\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"procedures\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"historic buildings\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Hidalgo also wants to retain the innovative cauldron placed in front of the Louvre museum as well as statues of illustrious women used during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999998917676353, \"rank\": 1.0823243702717846e-07, \"text\": \"Hid